description:
I am using 1.1rc1. This is a regression since rc1 and differs from javac. I suspect it may be related to a change in the underlying Eclipse compiler.
To reproduce the issue:
1. Create a class in the 'subpackage' subpackage:
   package subpackage;
   public class Test {
       public static void main(String[] args) {
           System.out.println('Hello');
       }
   }
2. Compile the class using the following command:
   ajc -d . subpackage\Test.java

Observed Behavior:
After compiling, a directory named 'subpackage' is created under the existing 'subpackage' directory.

Expected Behavior:
The 'subpackage' directory should not be created under the existing 'subpackage' directory.

The same behavior as javac is desired.
